summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Ensuring resources for JUnit**\\\\n\\\\nI need to ensure that the extension is auto-detected before running all tests. I should add the necessary resources. However, if the JUnit extension service is loaded by ServiceLoader in a native image, I have to provide a resource because it is static. I wonder if the native image supports it? It seems a JUnit plugin includes resources, so I need to write those out. I also need to ensure that any remaining Jakarta service is removed.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_WYdZUGMR4RWYhycx8aPmpFXz|fc_0484b4ce47d41ffa016a2645cf50f88196b0b27be9e3dfadb1\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/jakarta.el/jakarta.el-api/4.0.0/src/test/java/jakarta_el/jakarta_el_api/FactoryFinderTest.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"import org.junit.jupiter.api.AfterEach;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.BeforeEach;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\", \"newText\": \"import org.junit.jupiter.api.AfterEach;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.BeforeEach;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.BeforeEachCallback;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.extension.ExtensionContext;\\n\"}, {\"oldText\": \"public class FactoryFinderTest {\\n    private static final String EXPRESSION_FACTORY_PROPERTY = \\\"jakarta.el.ExpressionFactory\\\";\\n\", \"newText\": \"public class FactoryFinderTest {\\n    private static final String EXPRESSION_FACTORY_PROPERTY = \\\"jakarta.el.ExpressionFactory\\\";\\n    private static final String TEST_EXPRESSION_FACTORY = ServiceExpressionFactory.class.getName();\\n\"}]}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 2947, \"output\": 1232, \"cacheRead\": 31744, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 35923, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1780893106581, \"responseId\"